The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 13: The Reserve Bank today raised the limit for loans under the differential rate of interest scheme from Rs 6,500 to Rs 15,000 and for housing loans from Rs 5,000 to Rs 20,000 per beneficiary. The bank provides this assistance to low income groups at a concessional interest rate of 4 per cent. 

 Mumbai, June 13: The sensex fell 128 points to its lowest in about a month after investors resorted to heavy selling in bank, consumer goods, metal and energy stocks. The index settled at 14003.03, down 127.92 points from its previous close of 14130.95 points. 

 New Delhi, June 13: French food firm Groupe Danone will set up a dairy plant in Haryana through a joint venture with Japanese company Yakult Honsha as part of its Rs 136-crore investment plan in the country. 

 New Delhi, June 13: The Union cabinet is likely to consider a policy tomorrow, which suggests relaxation of norms to allow domestic carriers to fly abroad.

 New Delhi, June 13: Chemicals minister Ram Vilas Paswan has sent a letter to agriculture minister Sharad Pawar asking him to speed up the process of finalising the national pharmaceutical policy 2006.




